      "description": "This FD3S Mazda RX-7 is a museum-grade example of Japanese engineering, featuring the 13B-REW rotary powerplant with its sequential twin-turbocharger system performing to factory specifications. The vehicle retains its original 50:50 weight distribution and lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension, offering unparalleled cornering precision. Power is transferred through a tactile 5-speed manual transmission to a Torsen limited-slip differential. Every vacuum line, apex seal, and cooling system component has been scrutinized to ensure peak thermal efficiency and boost stability. The exterior and interior are free of any cosmetic or structural degradation, making this a definitive collector\u2019s piece for the rotary enthusiast.",
